<inglise> Council Regulation (EC) No 1105/2001 of 30 May 2001 amending Regulation (EEC) No 1911/91 on the application of the provisions of Community law to the Canary Islands </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 1105/2001, millega muudetakse m&auml;&auml;rust (EM&Uuml;) nr 1911/91 &uuml;henduse &otilde;iguse s&auml;tete kohaldamise kohta Kanaari saarte suhtes 30. mai 2001 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Act of Accession of Spain and Portugal, and in particular the first subparagraph of Article 25(4) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Hispaania ja Portugali &uuml;hinemisakti, eriti selle artikli 25 l&otilde;ike 4 esimest l&otilde;iku, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission(1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Opinion of the European Parliament(2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Opinion of the Economic and Social Committee(3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse majandus- ja sotsiaalkomitee arvamust (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Article 5(1) of Regulation (EEC) No 1911/91(4) established a transitional period which authorised the Spanish authorities to impose a tax on production and imports (APIM) on all products entering or produced in the Canary Islands. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1911/91 artikli 5 l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testati &uuml;leminekuperiood, mille jooksul Hispaania ametiasutusi volitati kehtestama tootmis- ja impordimakse (APIM) k&otilde;ikidele Kanaari saarte turule toodavatele v&otilde;i kohapeal valmistatavatele toodetele; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Article 6(1) of that Regulation established a transitional period to introduce progressively the Common Customs Tariff (CCT) in the Canary Islands. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) nimetatud m&auml;&auml;ruse artikli 6 l&otilde;ikega 1 kehtestati &uuml;leminekuperiood &uuml;hise tollitariifistiku j&auml;rkj&auml;rguliseks kohaldamiseks Kanaari saartele; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Both transitional periods expired on 31 December 2000. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) m&otilde;lemad &uuml;leminekuperioodid l&otilde;ppesid 31. detsembril 2000; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) In October and November 2000 the Spanish authorities requested that the said transitional periods and the measures introduced on the basis of Regulation (EEC) No 1911/91 be extended. </inglise>
<eesti> 4) oktoobris ja novembris 2000 taotlesid Hispaania ametiasutused k&otilde;nealuste &uuml;leminekuperioodide pikendamist ja m&auml;&auml;ruse (EM&Uuml;) nr 1911/91 kohaselt v&otilde;etud meetmete kehtivuse pikendamist; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) In July and October 2000, the Spanish authorities gave notification of a new tax which would apply to the Canary Islands and is intended to compensate for the handicaps referred to in Article 299(2) of the Treaty. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) juulis ja oktoobris 2000 teatasid Hispaania ametiasutused uuest Kanaari saarte suhtes kohaldatavast maksust, mis on ette n&auml;htud asutamislepingu artikli 299 l&otilde;ikes 2 osutatud halvemuste h&uuml;vitamiseks; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) The request contained documentation which indicated that even though the economic situation on the Canary Islands had improved during the transitional period, the full integration of the region would lead to a decline in industrial and commercial activity, and thus in employment, in the different sectors concerned. </inglise>
<eesti> 6) taotlus sisaldas t&otilde;endusmaterjali, millest n&auml;htub, et kuigi Kanaari saarte majanduslik olukord on &uuml;leminekuperioodi jooksul paranenud, kaasneks k&otilde;nealuse piirkonna t&auml;ieliku integreerimisega t&ouml;&ouml;stus- ja kaubandustegevuse allak&auml;ik ning seet&otilde;ttu v&auml;heneks ka asjaomaste sektorite t&ouml;&ouml;h&otilde;ive; </eesti>
<inglise> (7) However, in the short period available it was not possible to evaluate the full impact of the termination or modification of the existing measures on the economic and social situation of the Canary Islands. </inglise>
<eesti> 7) l&uuml;hikese aja jooksul ei olnud siiski v&otilde;imalik hinnata olemasolevate meetmete peatamise v&otilde;i muutmise t&auml;ielikku m&otilde;ju Kanaari saarte majanduslikule ja sotsiaalsele olukorrale; </eesti>
<inglise> (8) In order to ensure that the economic operators concerned are afforded a certain continuity in the legal framework affecting their business, it is appropriate to extend the said transitional periods by one year. </inglise>
<eesti> 8) tagamaks asjaomastele ettev&otilde;tjatele nende &auml;ritegevust m&otilde;jutava &otilde;igusliku raamistiku teatav j&auml;tkuvus, on asjakohane pikendada k&otilde;nealuseid &uuml;leminekuperioode &uuml;he aasta v&otilde;rra; </eesti>
<inglise> (9) Once the abovementioned evaluation has been completed, the Commission will make, if necessary, a new proposal taking into account the aims of Article 299(2) of the Treaty, </inglise>
<eesti> 9) kui eespool nimetatud hindamine on l&otilde;ppenud, teeb komisjon vajaduse korral uue ettepaneku, v&otilde;ttes arvesse asutamislepingu artikli 299 l&otilde;ike 2 eesm&auml;rke, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
